The days of Haitian food industry leading the rise of soy sauce stocks may not be long.





The days of Haitian food industry leading the rise of soy sauce stocks may not be long.



The outbreak of the epidemic, the catering industry caught off guard, the corresponding supply chain enterprises are also affected. But soy sauce companies seem to be an exception.

Since the start of February, Haitian (Url) , Zhongju Gaoxin (Url) and Qianhe (603027.Sh ) are UP-0.37% , 2.19% and 6.26% respectively. The market reaction was largely because "soy sauce is a necessary consumer product, not affected by the epidemic" .

Is that really true?

In fact, the catering channel is the largest sales channel in soy sauce industry. Our judgment is that the short-term impact of restaurant closures on the soy industry is a double-edged sword. But is the decisive factor which the pros and cons lies in the channel structure.

###Sales in the catering channel have plummeted

Soy Sauce sales channels are mainly divided into catering channels, home channels and food processing channels. Among them, catering channels not only accounted for the largest proportion (about 45%) , but also steadily increased; home channels and food processing channels accounted for about 30% and 25% respectively. According to statistics from China Industry Information Network, the food and beverage consumption per kilogram of food condiments is 1.57 times that of the household channel.

In the past, the Spring Festival was the peak season for the catering industry. Catering companies have been stocking up for years, and so have channel distributors. A sudden outbreak this year could leave restaurant companies and dealers with inventories piling up. Subsequently, dealers from the soy sauce industry will be less willing to take goods.

Under the impact of the food and beverage channel, the first to bear the brunt is the head of the soy sauce industry  Foshan Haitian food industry. Haitian low-end soy sauce to occupy the market, catering channel sales accounted for as high as 60% , merchants accounted for 30% , other channels accounted for only 10% . In contrast, Zhongju high-tech channel structure is more balanced, catering, business and other channels of the ratio of 2.5:4:3.5. Qianhewei main product positioning family consumption, its catering channels less than 10% , the impact of the outbreak of the smallest.

Haitian flavor industry has been using money before goods, in order to sell the way of production. Haitian will issue monthly sales plan to distributors and advance payment in weekly order form. However, during the Chinese New Year, dealers will also step up their stock restocking efforts, with accounts receivable at the end of 2017 and 2018 accounting for 18% and 19% of total sales for the year, about 10 percentage points higher than usual. Therefore, the Sea sky 2020 first quarter sales task is likely to be completed. Sales will be affected in the second quarter, because the dealers have a backlog of goods not digested, will affect the continued order. If the outbreak is brought under control by the end of March, the food and beverage industry will resume operations. Then, the epidemic will affect the Sea sky dining channel revenue time is about 2 months. Referring to the company's turnover of 4.67 billion yuan in the second quarter of 2019, assuming a 60% drop in demand from the catering channel, the company's operating income is expected to decline by about 16% in the second quarter of 2020, with an impact of about 4% for the whole year.

Image Credit: Interface News Research

Of course, there's another side to the coin.

The restaurant may be closed, but the meal is just what we need. During the outbreak, people stayed at home and the demand for cooking increased. That has spurred soy sauce consumption at the retail end.

Qianhewei commercial super channel accounted for about 90% , the increase in household consumption of soy sauce means that the company may achieve more than expected growth this year. In addition, Qianhe flavor industry in Hubei sales accounted for less, so affected by the epidemic situation is even less obvious. By the first three quarters of 2019, the sales revenue of condiments in the central region of Qianhe flavor industry was only 44 million yuan, while the western region, which has more concentrated channels, contributed 465 million yuan. ASSUME THAT HOUSEHOLD CONSUMPTION INCREASES BY 20 per cent over a period of two months. Well, Qianhe flavor industry turnover this year increased by about 4 percent.

The profit elasticity of qianhe flavor industry is also greater than the operating income. This is because the company is a high-end zero to add soy sauce as a top product. All along, high gross profit higher zero add soy sauce is the main driving force for the performance growth of Qianhe flavor industry. In the first three quarters of 2019, revenue from qianhe flavoring products was 780 million yuan, up 32.72 percent year-on-year, of which revenue from zero-additive products was about 451 million yuan, up 34.46 percent year-on-year. As the proportion of zero-adding products continues to expand, the gross profit rate of Qianhe flavor industry is expected to further improve.

###Will the myth of overvaluation be shattered?

Soy Sauce stocks have been criticized by the Haitian industry as the center of the "Baotuan" High Valuation.

In terms of the rolling price-earnings ratio, the current valuation of Haitian Flavor Industry is 55 times, Zhongju high-tech 45 times, Qianhe flavor industry 49 times. In the three quarters ending last year, the three companies'growth rate was the highest, at about 22% . It is worth noting that the three companies compared to 2018 earnings growth has been a significant decline. According to the PEG method, which is widely used in consumer stocks, we can judge whether the price-earnings ratio is overvalued by 1. With the distribution channels more and more intensive, after years of rapid growth of the soy sauce industry has shown fatigue.

However, from the Shanghai Stock Exchange Holdings, soy sauce shares this "group" High Valuation has not been loosened. Since February 3, the market value of the stake in the Shanghai stock connect has increased from 23.43% to 23.48% of the outstanding share capital.

The proportion of Zhongju Gaoxin and Qianhe flavor industry increased by 0.5 and 1.65 percentage points respectively. Their Holdings have increased accordingly. Visible, foreign capital is still bullish on soy sauce stocks, no signs of reduction.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Wind, Interface News Research

As the impact of the epidemic at this stage of the study is not clear, the logic of foreign ownership focus on long-term certainty, so there is no Haitian flavor performance or reduction of the operation. Once the performance of Haitian flavour industry growth is not expected, do not rule out short-term reduction of foreign investment. At that time, the collective high valuation of Soy Sauce stocks will be challenged.
